# Key Operational Challenges

The interviews identified several recurring barriers that may reduce implementation effectiveness:

- Weak coordination between HIV care, SUD care, medical services, and mental health support inside jail settings
- Provider stigma toward incarcerated individuals and people living with HIV or substance use disorders
- Cost constraints associated with implementing evidence-based practices
- Transportation barriers affecting continuity of care after release
- Difficulty adopting new technologies due to staff readiness and infrastructure limitations :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}

A practical interpretation is that even if the intervention model is strong, inconsistent coordination between organizations may cause individuals to lose access to follow-up care and support services.

